text: An earthquake with a preliminary magnitude of 4. 6 was recorded in the North Bay Thursday morning, according to the U.S. Geological Survey.  The quake occurred at 2 : 09 a. m. about 14 miles north - northeast of Healdsburg and had a depth of 1. 2 miles.
title: Magnitude 4. 6 Earthquake Shakes Up North Bay.
